						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Stone on Maṭhada-kaṇa.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription, the date of which is lost, is engraved in late characters. It states that the <hi rend="italic">Vaishṇava</hi> pontiff <hi rend="bold">Satyabōdha-Śrīpāda-oḍeya,</hi> disciple of <hi rend="bold">Satyapriya-Śripāda-Oḍeya,</hi> built a <hi rend="italic">maṭha</hi> in the village <hi rend="bold">Gōḍihaḷu</hi> and placed it in charge of <hi rend="bold">Kambāḷayya,</hi> son of <hi rend="bold">Koṇḍara Rudrappa.</hi> The characters belong to the <hi rend="bold">19th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
